added.title: Daycare of Rock
added.description: After believing he's turned Chef to stone Duncan sets his sights on ultimate chaos only to discover there's no joy in victory without an adversary.

added.title: Aches and Ladders
added.description: When MacArthur has a bad fall in the school, the kids' recollections of the event are just as weird as they are.

added.title: Truffle Season
added.description: It's Truffle Season, Apple and Onion are Truffle Hunters and they will stop at nothing to taste a truffle.

added.title: Lambporcini
added.description: Apple and Onion are very happy with their sweet new matching designer outfits they bought from known scam-artist Street Dog. That's until Chicken Nugget mistakes them for something they are not.

added.title: #Retreat!
added.description: Jessica Cruz and some super friends go on an overnight camping trip without their powers and are attacked by Poison Ivy and a horde of Plant Zombies!

added.title: #DinnerForFive
added.description: Barbara Gordon finds herself in a tight spot when an awkward dinner with a new friend's father turns into something so much more.

added.title: #LivingTheNightmare
added.description: When Zee's friends are held captive in their nightmares by a dream demon, she'll have to confront her own hidden insecurities, or risk the Super Hero Girls being trapped in a prison of their own fears forever.

added.title: #AllAboutZee
added.description: Zee Zatara is flattered when she meets an overeager admirer named Casey Krinsky, but soon realizes that "her biggest fan" wants much more than just an autograph.

added.title: #TweenTitans
added.description: Jessica Cruz is hired by billionaire playboy Bruce Wayne to chaperone young Dick Grayson's Metropolis birthday bash and brings Karen Beecher along to help, but the girls get more than they bargained for when the TWEEN party guests reveal their TITANic personalities.

added.title: Sir Tree House
added.description: Sir Tree is lonely, so Seth builds a treehouse in his branches to keep him company. It's such a hit, soon all of Fungietown moves in! But when the added weight strains Sir Tree, can Seth convince him to take better care of himself?

added.title: Lord Clawly Caper
added.description: When his medals are stolen during a Fungietown school assembly, Seth and Claudette start an investigation to find the culprit before everyone is thrown into the Triloknight's dungeon!

added.title: Schnorp
added.description: The Thunderkittens plug a new video game cartridge into Snarf only to learn that it didn't load a game, it loaded a whole new personality into their pal! Meet Schnorp, a kind Swedish man who loves the beauty of nature and collecting berries! Schnorp is loads of fun, but we're gonna want Snarf back, right?

added.title: Berb-cules
added.description: The ThunderCats finally sit the Berbils down and tell them they really shouldn't be building things for the Mutants anymore, it's time for the Berbils to stand up for themselves. The Berbils take this advice way too far and build a giant, building-sized, Berbil named Berbcules. Berb-cules takes back everything the Berbils ever built for the Mutants and everything they ever built for the ThunderCats! Now Panthro has to figure out a way to a defeat the most powerful invention the best little builders have ever built!

added.title: Pumm-Ra
added.description: Mumm-Ra plans to disguise himself as a Thunderian and infiltrate Cats' Lair, but the Ancient Spirits of Evil are mad at him and won't give him any magic today. No matter, Mumm-Ra knows what a ThunderCat looks like so he slaps on some awful, unconvincing, cat make up and heads to Cats' Lair to introduce himself!

added.title: King of the Machines
added.description: Panthro gets insecure when he finds out Barbastella has a history of dating royalty, so he tries to impress her by becoming "King of the Machines" and giving all the appliances in the Cats' Lair artificial intelligence.

added.title: Mandora Saves Christmas
added.description: Santa Claus is on the run from Mandora! Can the Thundercats help him get off Third Earth without getting caught? And can Santa Claus teach them a little something about this weird new holiday "Christmas"?

added.title: The Belly of the Beast
added.description: To repair the Land-Bounty, the ninja must retrieve a critical engine component that has been swallowed by a giant scarab beetle.

added.title: Booby-Traps, and How To Survive Them
added.description: The ninja team up with a reluctant Clutch Powers to enter a mysterious pyramid where they inadvertently unleash an ancient evil.

added.title: The News Never Sleeps!
added.description: Lil' Nelson takes a job as a paperboy, which is more difficult than it sounds in a city overrun by scorching Pyro Vipers and an evil Serpentine sorceress.

added.title: Ninja vs. Lava
added.description: The ninja find themselves trapped in a pyramid and must escape encroaching lava to warn NINJAGO City of a new Serpentine invasion.

added.title: Snaketastrophy
added.description: The Serpentine attack on NINJAGO City is seen from an unexpected perspective - entirely in the style of a live newscast delivered by Gayle Gossip and her cameraman.

added.title: From Below
added.description: Axel juggles looking after Luka and defending the house from Dr. Nautilus's latest abomination, a tentacle monster that attacks from every drain, pipe, and faucet in the building!

added.title: Winner Takes All
added.description: After months of training for Luchador Day, Axel needs Masko to coach him against a pair of uninvited competitors - Madcap and Dynamo!

added.title: Prepare for the Worst
added.description: Axel and Bobbie Blobby skip out on Sarge's disaster-prep drills, leaving enough of a gap in the team's defenses for a crow to swoop in and snatch Sarge! Feeling responsible, Axel leads the team on a search-and-rescue mission.

added.title: Stuck on You
added.description: Tired of Axel and the team taking him for granted, Masko tries to get kidnapped and ends up stuck to Dynamo, who's less than enthused with his rubbery new sidekick.

added.title: Opposites Attract
added.description: Claiming he's good at heart, Dynamo convinces Axel and the team to help him find a battery that can power his centrifuge and free him from Madtrap's control - but Bobbie Blobby isn't buying the baddie's story.

added.title: The Throw Down/Brawl for It All
added.description: The Throw Down: Lightning reveals his discovery of the Mind Core Cell but the AO arrive only to discover that Magnus has already beaten them to it./Brawl for It All: With both team's Bakugan knocked into a hibernation state by the Mind Core Cell only Dan and Magnus remain locked in a brawl for it all!

added.title: Career Opportunities/Punch the Clock
added.description: Career Opportunities: After defeating Magnus the AO get an offer of employment from a surprising source Philomena Dusk!/Punch the Clock: During a commercial to celebrate their joining the AAAnimus team Dan and the AO rebel before they sellout.

added.title: High Flying Hostiles/Backfire Brawl
added.description: High Flying Hostiles: While escorting the Mind Core Cell to AAAnimus Campus, the AO are attacked by Masato Kazami and his Body Guards./Backfire Brawl: Philomena's attempt to refocus the Mind Core Cell's power backfires and the AO must fight their fellow employees inside the AAAnimus Campus.

added.title: Hostile Take Over/The Big Bounce
added.description: Hostile Take Over: After more unsuccessful attempts to harness Core Cell energy the AO must battle their own Bakugan with AAAnimus tech in order to save them./The Big Bounce: The AO confront Philomena with concerns about her control over the Core Cell energy and are fired in the most unceremonious of manners.

added.title: Awesome vs. AAAnimus
added.description: Awesome V Aaanimus, Part 1: The AO plan on sneaking into AAAnimus and rescuing their Bakugan but are stopped by Benton who offers up an alternate plan./Awesome V Aaanimus, Part 2: The AO team up with Benton Dusk to recapture their stolen Bakugan and free the energy from the Mind Core Cell under the control of AAAnimus.

added.title: El Vientre del Monstruo
added.description: Para reparar el Land-Bounty, el ninja debe recuperar un componente crítico del motor que ha sido tragado por un escarabajo gigante.

added.title: Trampas y Como Sobrevivir a Ellas
added.description: El ninja se une a un clutch Powers renuente para entrar en una misteriosa pirámide donde desatan sin darse cuenta un antiguo mal.

added.title: Las Noticias Nunca Duermen
added.description: Lil 'Nelson toma un trabajo como repartidor de periódicos, lo cual es más difícil de lo que parece en una ciudad invadida por Pyro Vipers y una malvada hechicera serpentina.

added.title: Ninja Contra Lava
added.description: Los ninja se encuentran atrapados en una pirámide y deben escapar de la lava invasora para advertir a la ciudad de NINJAGO de una nueva invasión serpentina.

added.title: Serpientastrofe
added.description: El ataque de Serpentine en NINJAGO City se ve desde una perspectiva inesperada, completamente al estilo de un noticiero en vivo entregado por Gayle Gossip y su camarógrafo.

added.title: #Retirada
added.description: Jessica Cruz y algunas de sus mejores amigas salen a pasar una noche de campamento sin sus poderes, iy son atacadas por Hiedra Venenosa y una horda de plantas zombis!
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #CenaParaCinco
added.description: Barbara Gordon está en apuros cuando una cena incómoda el padre de una nueva amiga, se convierte en algo muy diferente.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Un Gran Enfrentamiento
added.description: Lightning por fin revela la ubicación de la Célula Núcleo, pero cuando Los Fantásticos llegan, descubren que Magnus fue más rápido que ellos.

added.title: La Batalla Decisiva
added.description: Luego de que la Célula Núcleo pusiera en estado de hibernación a los Bakugan de ambos equipos, Dan y Magnus se encuentran atrapados en una batalla donde lo apostarán todo.

added.title: Oportunidades Laborales
added.description: Después de derrotar a Magnus, los Fantásticos reciben una oferta de empleo de alguien inesperado... Filomena Dusk.

added.title: Un Nuevo Empleo
added.description: Durante un comercial para celebrar su contrato con el equipo AAAnimus, Dan y Los Fantásticos deciden rebelarse antes que traicionar sus principios.

added.title: Enemigos en el Aire
added.description: Cuando Los Fantásticos transportan la Célula Núcleo a las instalaciones de AAAnimus, son atacados por Masato Kazami y sus Guardaespaldas.

added.title: Un Experimento Fallido
added.description: El plan de Filomena Dusk para redireccionar la energía de la Célula Núcleo fracasa, y Los Fantásticos deben pelear contra sus propios compañeros de trabajo dentro de las instalaciones de AAAnimus.

added.title: Perdiendo el Control
added.description: Después de más intentos fallidos por aprovechar la energía la Célula núcleo, Los Fantásticos deben pelear contra sus propios Bakugan usando tecnología AAAnimus para salvarlos.

added.title: Despedidos
added.description: Los Fantásticos confrontan a Filomena, preocupados de que ella controle la energía de la Célula núcleo, y son despedidos de una forma poco profesional.

added.title: Fantasticos vs. AAAnimus Parte 1
added.description: Los Fantásticos planean infiltrarse a AAAnimus para rescatar a sus Bakugan, pero Benton los detiene para ofrecerles un plan alternativo.

added.title: Fantasticos vs. AAAnimus Parte 2
added.description: Los Fantásticos unen fuerzas con Benton Dusk para rescatar a sus Bakugan y liberar la energía de la Célula Núcleo que AAAnimus tiene bajo su control.

added.title: El Ganador se lo Lleva Todo
added.description: Después de meses de entrenamiento para el Día del Luchador, Axel necesita que Masko lo entrene contra un par de competidores no invitados: iMadcap y Dynamo!

added.title: Preparense Para Lo Peor
added.description: iAxel y Bobbie Blobby se saltan los simulacros de preparación para desastres de Sarge, dejando suficiente espacio en las defensas del equipo para que un cuervo se precipite y arrebata a Sarge! Sintiéndose responsable, Axel lidera al equipo en una misión de búsqueda y rescate.

added.title: Los Opuestos se Atraen
added.description: Afirmando que es bueno de corazón, Dynamo convence a Axel y al equipo para que lo ayuden a encontrar una batería que pueda alimentar su centrífuga y liberarlo del control de Madtrap, pero Bobbie Blobby no está comprando la historia del malo.

added.title: Desde las Profundidades
added.description: iAxel hace malabares cuidando a Luka y defendiendo la casa de la última abominación del Dr. Nautilus, un monstruo tentáculo que ataca desde cada drenaje, tubería y grifo del edificio!

added.title: Pegado a Ti
added.description: Cansado de que Axel y el equipo lo den por sentado, Masko intenta ser secuestrado y termina atrapado en Dynamo, que está menos que entusiasmado con su nuevo compañero de goma.
